main event: On June 9, 1965, multiple witnesses reported seeing an unidentified flying object near Bryte, California, including a bright, hovering, cigar-shaped object and lights in the sky.
interesting points: The first witness was Mrs. Warren, who described a cigar-shaped object hovering about 50 feet above the ground for 15 minutes before speeding away., Another witness, Mrs. Pearlie Harden, observed a large, bright round object with a bluish-white glow and saw it shoot straight up into the sky after being approached by a smaller jet-like object., The sightings were confirmed by several residents, indicating a significant level of public interest at the time., The USAF was notified of the sightings and conducted investigations, but no concrete conclusions were reached., Reports from the same date indicate at least two sightings involved flying objects with no sound and unusual movement patterns.
sighted object: a large, bright, round object and a cigar-shaped object
witness description: Mrs. Warren, Mrs. Pearlie Harden, and several other local residents
